    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8487" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σταθμός</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἵστημι</span>): any standingplace or thing that stands, hence
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">stall, pen</span>, or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">fold</span> for animals, also
          the shepherd's <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">lodge</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            2.470</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 19.377</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 17.20</span></i>; so <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">post,
            door-post</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 14.167</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 4.838</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">weight</span> for
          the balance, <i><span class="en">Il. 12.434</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">.—σταθμόνδε</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">to the stall,
            homeward</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
          9.451</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
